definition:
A man of the tribe of Judah living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at 1Ch.4.3; 
 son of: Hur (H2354); 
 brother of: Uri (H0221), Shobal (H7732H), Salma (H8007H), Hareph (H2780), Jezreel (H3157J), Ishma (H3457), Hazzelelponi (H6753), Penuel (H6439H) and Ezer (H5829) 
 § Idbash = "stout"
 one of the 3 sons of Abi-etam, a descendant of Judah
